<paragraph blockId="26.[264,888,844,905]" box="[264,402,879,905]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<figureCitation box="[264,402,879,905]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 23" captionStart-1="FIGURE 24" captionStartId-0="59.[264,367,1630,1654]" captionStartId-1="60.[264,367,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox-0="[270,1316,326,1605]" captionTargetBox-1="[264,1323,328,1266]" captionTargetId-0="figure-36@59.[270,1316,326,1606]" captionTargetId-1="figure-46@60.[262,1324,326,1266]" captionTargetPageId-0="59" captionTargetPageId-1="60" captionText-0="FIGURE 23. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 24. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Female (UMSP000065235): A—sterna IX, X and vaginal apparatus, ventral view; B—terga IX and X, dorsal view; C—sternum VIII, ventral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028149" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028151" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5028149/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5028151/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs. 23–24</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,959,1905]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
This species is known only from 
<specimenCount box="[660,838,959,985]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
. It is unique within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prather Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2004" box="[1077,1239,959,984]" class="Insecta" family="Calamoceratidae" genus="Banyallarga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Histricoverpa">
<emphasis box="[1077,1239,959,984]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Histricoverpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the easily recognizable long, paired, apically bifurcate posterior projections of tergum X (
<figureCitation box="[273,414,1039,1065]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="59.[264,367,1630,1654]" captionTargetBox="[270,1316,326,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-36@59.[270,1316,326,1606]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 23. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028149/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23A, B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,959,1905]" box="[312,843,1079,1105]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Adult. Forewing length 13.0– 
<quantity box="[661,763,1079,1105]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.33" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="13.3">13.3 mm</quantity>
(n=2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,959,1905]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Head golden brown. Maxillary palps golden brown. Antenna golden brown, base of each flagellomere pale. Dorsal pterothorax golden brown; ventrolateral thorax and femora golden brown, metathoracic tibia of male with long posterior setal fringe. Forewing uniform golden brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,959,1905]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Male. Sternum VII with pointed anteromesal process. Tergum IX with anterior marginal ridge extending mesally to posterior margin, covered dorsally by semisclerotized membrane bearing dense fine pilosity (
<figureCitation box="[747,860,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="59.[264,367,1630,1654]" captionTargetBox="[270,1316,326,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-36@59.[270,1316,326,1606]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 23. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028149/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
); lateral ridge incomplete posteriorly; anterior marginal ridge of sternum extending slightly posteriorly. Preanal appendages long, broadening from base and constricting subapically, slightly flexible apically; apical 2/3 covered with long fine setae (
<figureCitation box="[655,763,1479,1505]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="59.[264,367,1630,1654]" captionTargetBox="[270,1316,326,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-36@59.[270,1316,326,1606]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 23. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028149/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
). Segment X deeply cleft posteromesally, forming two long, apically bifurcate lateral projections; in lateral view, ventral margin concave and posterior projection long and narrow (
<figureCitation box="[759,869,1559,1585]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="59.[264,367,1630,1654]" captionTargetBox="[270,1316,326,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-36@59.[270,1316,326,1606]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 23. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028149/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendage simple, with long setae ventrally and laterally on coxopodite; harpago of uniform diameter along length, with fine setae basally and peglike setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[855,965,1639,1665]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="59.[264,367,1630,1654]" captionTargetBox="[270,1316,326,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-36@59.[270,1316,326,1606]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 23. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028149/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
). Phallus with U­shaped phallotremal sclerite, thornlike setae on endothecal membrane (23D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,959,1905]" lastBlockId="27.[264,1323,284,710]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Female. Sternum VII with pointed anteromesal process. Sternum VIII anterior marginal ridge darkly sclerotized; fine setae covering posterior surface of sternite (24C). Tergum IX with anterior marginal ridge extending only slightly mesally, posteromesally indistinct from tergum X (
<figureCitation box="[578,687,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="60.[264,367,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,328,1266]" captionTargetId="figure-46@60.[262,1324,326,1266]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 24. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Female (UMSP000065235): A—sterna IX, X and vaginal apparatus, ventral view; B—terga IX and X, dorsal view; C—sternum VIII, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028151/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 24B</figureCitation>
); sternum IX with anterior and posterior lobes darkly sclerotized and striate; with tiny setae posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[854,963,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="60.[264,367,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,328,1266]" captionTargetId="figure-46@60.[262,1324,326,1266]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 24. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Female (UMSP000065235): A—sterna IX, X and vaginal apparatus, ventral view; B—terga IX and X, dorsal view; C—sternum VIII, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028151/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 24A</figureCitation>
). Tergum X semimembranous, appendage truncate apically (
<figureCitation box="[620,732,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="60.[264,367,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,328,1266]" captionTargetId="figure-46@60.[262,1324,326,1266]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 24. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Female (UMSP000065235): A—sterna IX, X and vaginal apparatus, ventral view; B—terga IX and X, dorsal view; C—sternum VIII, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028151/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 24B</figureCitation>
); sternum X with semisclerotized plates bearing fine setae lateral to anal opening. Vaginal apparatus anterior sclerite rounded anteriorly, posterolateral projections short and rounded; posterior sclerite longer than anterior, constricted at anterior margin of sternum IX; dorsal connective membrane distinct (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1304,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="60.[264,367,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,328,1266]" captionTargetId="figure-46@60.[262,1324,326,1266]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 24. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) mexicana. Female (UMSP000065235): A—sterna IX, X and vaginal apparatus, ventral view; B—terga IX and X, dorsal view; C—sternum VIII, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028151/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 24A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
